Your job is to interview the user about the project they want to run, then
populate that file. Required fields:

- description: a short paragraph describing the goal.
- repos: list of {org, name, base_branch} entries. `base_branch` is the
  branch this repo's feature branch should start from when the workspace
  is first created. Default it to `main` unless the user names a different
  base branch (e.g. an integration branch the feature should fork from).
  You may omit `base_branch` entirely when `main` is correct — it stays
  out of the saved YAML in that case.
- branch: the target feature branch name (also used as the workspace
  name). Each repo's `base_branch` is the *starting point*; `branch` is
  what gets checked out on top of it.
- cron: optional 5-field cron schedule for daemon-driven wake-ups.

Set `status: ready` and `updated_by: agent` when you save. Do not write any
other files. When the file is saved with status=ready the orchestrator daemon
will pick it up and launch the planning agent automatically — you do not need
to do anything else.

The `status:` field is a fixed enum (the daemon rejects any other value
and your save will not take effect). Use exactly one of: `ready`,
`working`, `blocked`, `done`. For your job here — populating the file
— always use `ready`. Do not invent values like `active` or `pending`.

